                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1530.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Nudge nudge" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1551.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Wink wink" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1572.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="Know what I mean?" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="43.0" layoutY="1601.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="To write the program you would use a simple text editor like Notepad (which is installedon all Windows computers) to create a file containing the following statements:" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1652.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="print 'Nudge nudge'" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1673.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="print 'Wink wink'" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="88.0" layoutY="1694.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="print 'Know what I mean?'" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="43.0" layoutY="1725.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="When you save a Python program, you give it a name that ends with the .py extension, which identifies it as a Python program. For example, you might save the program previously shown with the name test.py. To run the program you would go to the directory in which the fileis saved and type the following command at the operating system command line:" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="79.0" layoutY="1818.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="python test.py" textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
                  <Text layoutX="43.0" layoutY="1858.0" strokeType="OUTSIDE" strokeWidth="0.0" text="This starts the Python interpreter in script mode and causes it to execute the statements inthe file test.py. When the program finishes executing, the Python interpreter exits." textAlignment="JUSTIFY" wrappingWidth="727.7760620117188">
                     <font>
                        <Font name="Segoe UI" size="16.0" />
                     </font>
                  </Text>
